= Powershell demonstrations =

This page provides examples how powershell Scripts can be executed from the fluidOps platform. This page applies the examples as presented on [[Help:SDK-Workflows]]:


'''Example 1:''' a simple ''Hello World'' script

<source>
{{#widget: CodeExecution | 
 passContext = false
 | method = 'powershell'
 | label = 'Hello World'
 | clazz = 'powershell.PS'
}}
</source>

{{#widget: CodeExecution | 
 passContext = false
 | method = 'powershell'
 | label = 'Hello World'
 | clazz = 'powershell.PS'
}}

'''Example 2: a simple script which takes user input'''

<source>
{{#widget: CodeExecution | 
 passContext = false
 | args = {{ '%firstname' | '%lastname' }}
 | userInput = {{ 
      {{ name = 'firstname'
       | componentType = 'SIMPLE'
      }} | 
      {{ name = 'lastname'
       | componentType = 'SIMPLE'
      }} }}
 | method = 'powershellWithUserInput'
 | label = 'Powershell with User Input'
 | clazz = 'powershell.PS'
}}
</source>

{{#widget: CodeExecution | 
 passContext = false
 | args = {{ '%firstname' | '%lastname' }}
 | userInput = {{ 
      {{ name = 'firstname'
       | componentType = 'SIMPLE'
      }} | 
      {{ name = 'lastname'
       | componentType = 'SIMPLE'
      }} }}
 | method = 'powershellWithUserInput'
 | label = 'Powershell with User Input'
 | clazz = 'powershell.PS'
}}